1
00:00:00,218 --> 00:00:01,745
Crossing the Rubicon means passing

2
00:00:01,745 --> 00:00:03,200
the point of no return.

3
00:00:03,418 --> 00:00:05,600
It comes from Julius Caesar,

4
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,273
approaching a small river on Italy's

5
00:00:07,273 --> 00:00:08,364
northern boundary.

6
00:00:08,581 --> 00:00:10,617
Roman law forbade any governor from

7
00:00:10,617 --> 00:00:12,435
leading troops into Italy while

8
00:00:12,435 --> 00:00:13,890
still in command.

9
00:00:14,107 --> 00:00:15,634
If Caesar crossed with the

10
00:00:15,634 --> 00:00:17,452
Thirteenth Legion, he became an

11
00:00:17,452 --> 00:00:19,125
outlaw and invited death.

12
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:21,024
On the night of January tenth or

13
00:00:21,024 --> 00:00:23,497
eleventh, forty-nine BC, he chose

14
00:00:23,497 --> 00:00:24,733
to cross anyway.

15
00:00:24,951 --> 00:00:26,333
That decision triggered civil war

16
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:27,715
and opened Caesar's path to

17
00:00:27,715 --> 00:00:28,588
dictatorship.

18
00:00:28,806 --> 00:00:30,842
So today, crossing the Rubicon still

19
00:00:30,842 --> 00:00:32,297
means committing to a risky course

20
00:00:32,297 --> 00:00:33,461
with no return.
